    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-14T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-14T19:00:00-05:00" n="404"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856d.00/12–1449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-14T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 14, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4464. Fol sent Batavia:<note n="1" xml:id="d404fn1">622, December 15, noon; it
                        was repeated as 923 to Moscow, 1137 to The Hague, and 908 to New
                        Delhi.</note> “Sov veto of Canad resolution calling upon <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> to congratulate Neth and <gloss target="#t_Indo1"
                        >Indo</gloss>s on successful conclusion <gloss target="#t_RTC1">RTC</gloss>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d404fn2">For text of Canadian resolution of December 12, see
                            <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, <hi rend="italic">4th yr.,
                        Suppl</hi>. (Oct–Dec.), p. 13; for account of <gloss target="#t_SC1"
                            >SC</gloss> action, see Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                            >Bulletin</hi>, December 19, 1949, p.934.</note> reveals true Sov
                    attitude toward genuine nationalism <gloss target="#t_SEA1">SEA</gloss>. You
                    shld seek opportunity make this point clear to Hatta and other <gloss
                        target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> leaders. You shld emphasize that Sov and its
                    satellites were alone in rejecting a settlement which provides complete
                    independence to <gloss target="#t_USI1">USI</gloss> only because leaders of
                        <gloss target="#t_USI1">USI</gloss> have demonstrated that they will not
                    submit to fon domination, Commie or otherwise. You shld point out that Sov veto
                    constitutes repudiation of policies adopted at New Delhi Conference earlier this
                    year.</p>
                <p>Pls advise <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> your opinion of effect Sov veto
                    on (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) acceptability terms of agreement <gloss
                        target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss>; (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) attitude <gloss
                        target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> leaders; (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) attitude
                    Hatta and Sukarno toward recognition Chi Commies; (<hi rend="italic">d</hi>)
                    attitude <gloss target="#t_USI1">USI</gloss> Govt toward exchange diplomatic
                    representation USSR.”</p>
                <p>Pls give <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> your views foregoing after
                    consultation <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
